annotationA: Multifunctional protein ADE2; Ade5 is an essential enzyme in the pathway for de novo synthesis of the purine nucleotide inosine monophosphate (IMP). IMP is the precursor for purine nucleotides required for nucleic acids, energy transfer, cell signaling, and coenzymes; In the N-terminal section; belongs to the SAICAR synthetase family
annotationB: C-1-tetrahydrofolate synthase, cytoplasmic; Formate-tetrahydrofolate ligase activity; ATP binding; methenyltetrahydrofolate cyclohydrolase activity; methylenetetrahydrofolate dehydrogenase (NADP+) activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: folic acid-containing compound biosynthetic process; oxidation-reduction process; one-carbon metabolic process; In the C-terminal section; belongs to the formate-- tetrahydrofolate ligase family
